Story time! 14 years ago while I was in the Army I walked upon this western diamondback baby rattler. He bit me and wouldn’t let go. At the time I was deep in the Mojave desert which required a medevac. After being given the wrong meds the venom had progressed way faster than it should have.  As my luck would have it there was a dust/wind storm as the medevac was trying to land which caused some delays. I wish I could remember the 1SG who stuck by my side and told me I’d be ok, even when I didn’t think it was true. Anyway, finally made it to the army hospital and took all the antivenin and had to be evac’d again to a snake bite unit in southern Cali where I stayed a week until my platelets returned to normal. I returned about 2 weeks later for a follow up so they could check my blood once more.  To my surprise they told me I was pregnant. The doctor comes in and tells me that if the baby even made it to term there would be severe complications and likely deformities and death after birth. At that time I decided that it would not be fair to anyone and made the decision to not go through with the pregnancy. Part of me died that day. 

My then 1SG dried out the snake and brought it to me as a souvenir 😂. So I’ve had his head tucked away in my jewelry box for many years. Kind of like the last laugh. 

Fast forward to last year……. I randomly meet a shaman who knows nothing about me, he immediately tells me that my soul is intertwined with a snake……… 🥹😳 He goes on to tell me that my physical body flashes with scales and that there is something wild attached to my spirit. 

Yesterday, I find the snakehead and decide to cast him into an eternal resin tomb in which I will wear him as a reminder from now on. #healing #life #snakebite #loss #loveyourselftoday #forgiveness #timeheals #forgiveyourself #resinjewelry #resin #westerndiamondbackrattlesnake #spirits

This is one of the only places that can bring me back sometimes. Thankful for my family.  Thankful for the fresh air. Thankful for this view that’s somewhat of a savior.  Putting my feet into the sand is relaxing and recharging, and helpful on this self healing journey. Deep breathes of the ocean air puts me at ease as I reflect on the things I know I cannot change. 

Love and take care of yourselves people. It’s important. #mentalhealth #mentalwellness #healing #healingjourney #acceptance #loveyourself

Just a reminder to keep going! Even when you don’t want to. This was one of multiple spinal surgeries I have had from an Army injury. I wanted to give up. Not only was I in physical pain that quite literally made me wish I was dead, but I was also struggling with severe depression and ptsd. I remember telling myself I would be ok and not believe it. Kind of like when I had to lie to someone dying in front of me and telling them everything would be ok.  They didn’t believe it, I didn’t believe it, but it was comforting. Rise from the ashes & live life the way you want #broken #keeponkeepingon #loveyourself #takecareofyourself #yourlifematters #mentalhealth

One of the last couple years I was on the police dept I was called to check on an elderly man who may have been feeling sad. Once I got there I recognized him from the Walmart shooting that took place a couple years prior. He had lost his wife during the massacre and didn’t know where he was headed after her death. Just lost without her. He and I talked for some time and before I left he said “your personality is just like my beautiful wife and I miss her terribly. She was loving and kind and we took care of each other the better part of our lives. She would have loved you and I want you to have this” and handed me her wind-chime. I’m not one to accept gifts but as he was holding it out with tears in his eyes I couldn’t tell him no.  So Miss Margie’s wind chime has been packed away until now 🩵. It finally has a home where it can blow in the breeze. Mr. Basco passed away in 2021 and I know he couldn’t wait to be reunited with the love of his life. #soulmate #angels #meanttobe #crisisintervention #restinpeace #chapters

As a kid growing up I watched my Uncle Bill serve the people of our community year after year, he was always helping someone or some animal. Lol. Uncle Bill was my role model growing up & I wanted to be just like him. When I graduated high school I was too young to become a deputy right away like him so he told me to go to the military, do a couple years &come back to Russell county to follow his footsteps. I was dead set on doing just that. When I left for the army in 2004 I ended up liking it so much I stay for 10 years until I was injured &retired. After getting out of the military in El Paso, Texas I decided to continue my childhood dream Bill had planted in me. I became an El Paso Police officer & had an amazing career. From being on rookie status to becoming a field training officer, training & mentoring rookies myself I was fulfilling my dreams. I went on to becoming a well known officer on the hit tv show Live PD where I got to give the common person an inside look at the ugly reality police officers live each & every day. Once that chapter closed I went on to be a full time crisis negotiator where I worked primarily with people in mental health crisis, whether that meant spending time talking with someone experiencing depression, talking someone off a bridge, or talking a gun out of someone’s hands. It all originated with my Uncle Bill, the way he cared for his fellow man shaped me as an adult. When responding to the Walmart shooting that claimed so many innocent lives, he was the one I called because there were so many unknowns that day & knew what I was about to witness would change me forever. He simply & calmly told me it was time to do what I had trained all these years for. And I did. We all did.  My career as a law enforcement officer came to a close in 2021 when I resigned to focus on my family & follow my next dream of becoming a business owner. 
I have since then moved back to Russell County & I couldn’t be more excited that Bill is running for Sheriff. I am confident there’s not anyone more ready, prepared, selfless, professional & competent than Bill Watson. 🇺🇸 #sheriff #vote
